New China Review: Making Outstanding Returning Migrant Workers a Living Force for Rural Renewal - Xinhua News
Talent is the key to rural revitalization.
Where to find talent?
The outstanding group of returning migrant workers is an indispensable force.
Xinhua News Agency
Chengdu, July 26, Xinhua News Agency (Xinhua)
Zhang Xiong, 34 years old, lives in Orchard Village, Meishan City, Sichuan. In 2010, he quit his job in Beijing with a monthly salary of tens of thousands and returned home to start a business.
After several years of hard work, the grape-growing family farm he runs now has an annual income of more than one million yuan, has become a well-known rich leader, and has also been selected to join the team of the village "two committees."
In recent years, inspired by a series of policies to support and benefit farmers, such as national poverty eradication and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return home to start their own businesses, activating a pool of spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, the most populous and labor-exporting province in the western part of China, has implemented the "Outstanding Migrant Workers Reduction and Training Project" due to the favorable situation. In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries, 61,000 village reserve forces and more than 20,000 development party members were generated from the outstanding migrant workers, providing a strong guarantee for winning the battle against poverty and implementing the rural revitalization strategy.
Whether it is well-off or not depends on the country.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged laborers in China's rural areas have gone out to work to increase their incomes, and some have set up their own enterprises through hard work.
However, it has also objectively led to the emergence of "empty-mindedness" in rural areas to different degrees, especially the weakening of rural grass-roots organizations. The secretaries of village Party branches and the ranks of Party members have shown the characteristics of "one old and one low," that is, they are old and have low educational qualifications, the ranks of leaders of village Party organizations are not strong, and the problems are prominent.
If rural talents and other factors have been flowing to the cities in one direction, and the countryside is in the state of "blood loss" and "anemia" for a long time, revitalization is an empty word.
To attract back those migrant workers who are capable, conscious and interested in serving their hometown, guide them to return home to start their own businesses and become leaders in getting rich, train them into Party members and village cadres on the basis of merit, and enrich the cadre at the grass-roots level, which is the solution to the root causes of the disconnect between the rural Party membership team and the grass-roots Party organizations.
Excellent migrant workers should be brought back, and they should be allowed to stay and do well.
In recent years, Sichuan has begun to pay close attention to the Party building of migrant workers and, on the basis of strict selection criteria, has established institutional mechanisms such as targeted referral, service guarantee, training, empowerment, selection and use of outstanding migrant workers, so that they can improve their abilities, have job security and have hope in life, truly establish roots in the countryside and have a sense of accomplishment in starting a business.
This year is the closing year of the decisive fight against poverty eradication. Talent is the key factor to connect the fight against poverty eradication with rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of outstanding returning migrant workers and, through comprehensive measures, turn them into a team and living army that can stay, fight and cannot take away, so as to provide strong organizational guarantee and talent support for rural poverty eradication, prosperity, development and revitalization.
