Black land "planted" for agricultural modernization - Xinhua
Harbin, July 26, Xinhua News Agency (Xinhua)
In the middle of summer, two spraying planes passed the 10,000-acre high-yield demonstration field at the Second Operation Station of the Fifth Management Area of Friendship Farm, forming two white lines. The big words "the first field in the world" planted with black rice seedlings in the green field stood out.
Kong Lingqiang, the station director of the operation station, said that this kind of aircraft can spray medicine on more than 6,000 acres of cultivated land a day, which is about eight times more efficient than drones and hundreds of times more efficient than artificial ones.
This farm is located in the territory of Friendship County, Heilongjiang Province, the largest grain-producing province in China. From the sound of "rice cutting" in the past to the sound of "rumbling" today, Chinese traditional farming and farms have transformed in this black soil belt.
In addition to airplanes, satellites are also used in the modern agricultural production of Friendship Farm.
Kong Lingqiang introduced that, on the one hand, they use satellite remote sensing technology to accurately apply fertilizer, reduce agricultural input and reduce pollution; on the other hand, satellite navigation technology can improve the standardized operation level of agricultural machinery in the field.
In the course of rice production this year, the farm expanded the operating area of satellite navigation unmanned transplanting technology from 3,000 mu last year to 30,000 mu.
This technology can make seedlings more evenly planted, maximize the use of sunlight and cultivated land resources, and save 16 yuan per acre of labor cost.
Farms have tried new technologies such as informatization and intelligence in agricultural production, forming the largest group of agricultural machinery in China from the ground to the sky.
According to statistics, the total holdings of farm machinery are 49,000 units (pieces), and the comprehensive mechanization rate in the field has reached 99.8%.
The operation of agricultural machinery will achieve 100% GPS satellite navigation, 100% precision seeding in dry fields and 100% high-power locomotive operation in dry fields.
"Green agriculture, smart agriculture and digital agriculture are the directions of agricultural modernization."
said Liu Hualian, director of Friendship Farm.
The key to agricultural modernization lies in scientific and technological progress.
Agricultural reclamation in Heilongjiang, represented by farms, has played a demonstration and leading role in modern large-scale agriculture "aircraft carrier" in recent years, and has initially established a modern agricultural industry system dominated by large-scale cultivation, standardized production and industrial management.
On the outskirts of Friendship County, there is an agricultural machinery exhibition park covering an area of 350,000 square meters.
More than 140 sets (pieces) of agricultural machinery and tools introduced and used in Heilongjiang agricultural reclamation over the years are centrally displayed here.
These agricultural tools and farms have witnessed the development of China's agricultural modernization.
Xie Xiaojia for everyone -- Hefei, Anhui Province, Jiangkou River Union people of all ethnic groups transfer direct attack - Xinhua
Hefei, Xinhua News Agency, July 26, Question: Xie Xiaojia for everyone -- People from all ethnic groups in Jiangkou River Union, Hefei, Anhui Province
Xinhua News Agency reporters Chen Shangying, Wang Liwu and Liu Xia Village
At 4 o'clock in the afternoon of July 25, Fu Kunbao, wearing rubber shoes covered with mud, went from the front room to the back room, and his wife Zhou Yan were busy picking up things.
"After receiving the call from the village cadres asking for the transfer, I was still picking grass in the field."
Fu Kunbao said that he had transferred more than 60 acres of land and planted rice. At present, the growth rate is good. "Yesterday, he also took medicine and didn't clean up the tools or anything."
Fu Kunbao pointed to the pesticide sprayer placed in the corner. "No one wants his home to be flooded. Leave his home for everyone."
In order to cope with the continuous high water level pressure of Chaohu Lake and the possible heavy rainfall, Hefei City, Anhui Province, is ready to open the Jiangkou River Union River to store water on the 26th.
Jiangkou River Union is located in Faixi County, next to the Chaohu embankment.
Thousands of villagers involved in Yan Dian Township and Sanhe Town need to be transferred.
As of 16: 00 on the 25th, the water level of Chaohu Lake, the fifth largest freshwater lake in China, remained at a high level of 13.2 meters, exceeding the guaranteed water level by 0.7 meters.
Fu Kun Bao's kitchen is clean and clean. There is a basin of pumpkin dishes on the table, eggs and some brine in the fridge.
"I didn't expect to move. The water in Jiangkou River looks good now."
Zhou Yan said that the home is a bungalow, and some big objects have not yet thought about where to put them.
"Pack up the valuable items first. Large items such as refrigerators and TV sets can be placed in the homes of neighbors or relatives on high ground for the time being."
Wang Lizhong, a village cadre, advised Fu Kun Bao.
Wang Lijing was responsible for the transfer and resettlement of 13 villagers, and one family notified each other to confirm the resettlement plan for each.
The nearest settlement to Fu Kun Bao's home is Su Xiaoxue, Yan Dian Township, about 2 kilometers away.
In addition to large items, Fu Kunbao and his family also had more than 1,000 kilos of grain and some newly bought furniture.
"The grain is ready to be dragged to the house of relatives, and the furniture cannot be moved."
After discussion, the husband and wife put a stool under the newly bought bed and raised the bed by about half a meter.
At 6 o'clock in the afternoon, Fu Kunbao began to use a tricycle to transport things to his relatives' home. Zhou Yan continued to clean up at home.
After 11 o'clock in the evening, the husband and wife looked at the front and back of the house, pulled up the switch and prepared to go to the resettlement site.
"I hope the water will recede soon."
Fu Kunbao said.
At 9: 30 a.m. on July 26, the reporter saw at the scene of Jiangkou River Union that the local people had made all the preparations before the flood separation.
