Church fire in Nantes, France: Parish volunteers admit to setting fire to the church.
CNS, July 26: According to foreign media reports, on July 18, the famous St. Peter and St. Paul's Cathedral, a treasure of religious historical buildings in Nantes, France, was severely damaged in a fire, and the organ was completely destroyed.
On the 26th local time, the prosecutor of Nantes announced that a parish volunteer who was in charge of guarding the cathedral had been charged with "arson and destruction."
He has admitted that he started the fire in the church.
According to the report, local prosecutor Senas said that the 39-year-old parish volunteer from Rwanda admitted that he set fire to three places in the cathedral at night.
The man's lawyer said that the arsonist regretted doing such a thing.
This man entered France several years ago through the way of asylum. He was sheltered in the parish where the fire occurred and taken in the church.
The prosecution pointed out that recently, he tried to renew his visa and was talking with the police.
However, the church said it still couldn't believe that the believer, who was usually very kind and smiling but didn't speak much, would destroy the church he loved so much.
On the day of the fire on July 18, the volunteer was questioned and investigated by the police because of the illogical problems in the narrative, but he was later released.
The picture shows firefighters at the scene.
On the evening of the 25th, he was summoned again because the professional engineer of the laboratory of the Paris Central Police Department obtained new evidence.
This time, the man admitted his act of arson.
It is reported that if convicted of intentional arson and destruction, the suspect may face 10 years' imprisonment and a fine of 150,000 euros.
It is reported that the fire caused serious damage to St. Pierre and St. Paul's Cathedral. The organ in the church was completely destroyed and the stained glass windows behind the organ were also seriously damaged.
According to Brunet, the chief architect of the French historic preservation building, it is conservatively estimated that the restoration of Nantes Cathedral will take at least three years.
Comprehensive news: US unilateralism undermines bilateral relations International public opinion supports China's countermeasures against the US - Xinhua News
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, July 26, Xinhua News Agency, foreign correspondent: On the morning of July 24, the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs informed the US Embassy in China that China had decided to revoke the establishment and operation license of the US Consulate General in Chengdu and put forward specific requirements for the Consulate General to stop all business and activities.
International public opinion believes that the unilateral measures taken by the United States have caused serious distress to China-US relations. It is legitimate and necessary for China to respond to the unreasonable provocations of the United States and take countermeasures.
Andrés Bolquez, director of the Center for China Studies of the Institute of International Studies of the University of Chile, said that the unilateral measures of the United States have destroyed the bridge of understanding between the Chinese and American peoples and put the relationship between the two major powers in crisis.
China's notification to the United States to close its Consulate General in Chengdu is a countermeasure to the unilateral measures taken by the United States and is in line with diplomatic practice.
Patricio Giusto, a professor at the Catholic University of Argentina and director of the Argentina-China Research Center, believes that China's above-mentioned decision is a legitimate and necessary countermeasure to the previous provocations of the United States and is not aimed at ordinary Americans.
The United States is trying to divert the attention of the American public by pressuring China to cover up its weak response to the new crown epidemic.
Bambang Sulyono, chairman of the Asian Innovation Research Center, an Indonesian think tank, said that the provocative diplomatic posture taken by the United States has caused serious distress to China-US relations and the bilateral relations are facing serious challenges.
China's notification to the United States to close its Consulate General in Chengdu is a normal countermeasure, in line with diplomatic practice, and reflects not only China's principled position of firmly safeguarding its own interests, but also the rational and beneficial nature of China's diplomacy.
Tanzania commentator Francis Semwinza said that China's above-mentioned decision is a legitimate and necessary response to the US provocation.
The US should take the initiative to improve its relations with China and stop interfering in China's internal affairs.
The United States should focus on how to achieve economic and political win-win results with China and how to benefit the two peoples and the international community as a whole.
Ali Youssef, executive director of the Sudan-based Federation of Arab-Chinese Friendship Associations, said that the countermeasures forced by China were a legitimate and necessary response to the unreasonable actions of the United States, in line with international law and the basic norms governing international relations, as well as with diplomatic practices.
Previously, the US requested the closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston, which seriously violated international law and the basic norms governing international relations.
It is hoped that the US side will revoke the previous relevant decisions and create the necessary conditions for the return of bilateral relations to normal.
Singapore's Lianhe Zaobao published an editorial saying that the larger strategic intention of the United States is to encircle China and prevent its continued rise.
Facing the pressure of the United States, China is very reluctant to see the deterioration of China-US relations, but has to take countermeasures.
