Xinhua News Agency, Guangzhou, July 26 (reporter Mao Xin) The reporter learned from the Guangdong Maritime Police Bureau that recently, the bureau, in conjunction with the Guangzhou Customs and public security departments, cracked down a super-large refined oil smuggling gang. It was preliminarily verified that the gang had smuggled about 120,000 tons of refined oil since 2019, with a case value of about 800 million yuan and tax evasion of about 240 million yuan.
The Guangdong Maritime Police Bureau and the anti-smuggling department of the Customs have jointly and gradually mapped out the division of personnel and organizational structure of the gang.
