It is understood that a total of eight ships and two helicopters were deployed in the joint operation, which was divided into multiple action groups to carry out a chain-wide attack on smuggling at sea and illegal operations on land, and all 35 major criminal suspects were brought to the case.
The case is currently under further investigation.
The relevant person in charge of the Guangdong Maritime Police Bureau said that it would continue to maintain a high-pressure posture in the future, crack down on all kinds of illegal and criminal smuggling activities at sea and maintain good order in the maritime areas under its jurisdiction.
Hurricane "Hanna" landed in the U.S. or caused river surge and flash floods.
On July 26, China News Service (CNS) reported that at 5: 00 p.m. local time on July 25, Hurricane "Hannah" landed in Texas, bringing strong winds, torrential rain, river surge and possibly life-threatening flash floods to Texas.
The National Hurricane Center said that Hurricane Hanna is expected to carry heavy rainfall across parts of southern and northeastern Texas, which may cause some streams to soar and life-threatening flash floods.
According to the report, the area most seriously affected by Hurricane Hanna is from the south of Corpus Christi to the mouth of the Rio Grande River, while widespread flash floods may erupt in the Rio Grande Valley.
