Xinhua News Agency, Nanchang, July 26 (Guo Dongming, Xiong Liang) The Recruitment Office of the Jiangxi Provincial People's Government has recently made it clear that priority will be given to the recruitment of individuals or their children who have performed outstanding in the flood rescue and disaster relief mission who meet the requirements for recruitment and have passed both the medical examination and the political examination.
"After the young recruits are registered, we will give priority to the recruitment after verification by the community where the young recruits live, the street armed forces department and the Liuyang District Recruitment Office."
Wang Hui, vice minister of the Ministry of People's Armed Forces of Youyang District, Jiujiang City, said that due to the flood, they had concentrated three days to organize the medical examination of young candidates from the 25th.
