Zhou Jingfan said that he had a dream of joining the army since he was a child, and the anti-flood campaign strengthened his determination to join the military camp.
Jiujiang City also takes flood prevention and rescue as a "living teaching material" for recruitment propaganda. Taking the community as a unit, they call on young conscripts to volunteer to take part in tasks such as patrolling and checking embankments and on duty, to understand the nature and purpose of the people's army and to strengthen their confidence in joining the army and reporting to the country.
Luo Jiuyu, Political Commissar of the Ministry of People's Armed Forces, Youyang District, Jiujiang City, said that by giving priority to the recruitment of soldiers, he hoped to encourage more young recruits and create a good social atmosphere in which it was glorious to take part in the task and join the army.
