An upgraded version of the Russian helicopter gunship card-52M went out for the first time at the end of the year.
MOSCOW, July 25, 2020 / PRNewswire / -- According to the plan of the Russian Ministry of Defense, the upgraded version of the Russian helicopter gunship (hereinafter referred to as Wushi) Ka-52, the Ka-52M, will be renovated and replaced for the first time in December this year, and the aircraft will be greatly improved in reconnaissance, communications and weapons performance.
According to a recent report by the Russian News, the development contract of the Wuzhika-52M, named "Super Alligator," was signed by the Russian military and military industrial units in April last year. At present, the first two upgraded Wuzhika-52M are undergoing renovation and replacement at the Far East Helicopter Manufacturing Plant of the Russian "Progress" Aerospace Corporation, and its national testing and improvement will be completed by October 2022.
According to the Russian experts familiar with the above-mentioned upgrade work, the "predecessor" of the "super alligator", the Wuzhika-52, was officially installed in November 2011. The model revealed some weaknesses in its use. The purpose of the upgrade is to "fill the shortboard".
It is reported that compared with the Ka-52, the Ka-52M will partially adopt new protective materials that do not increase weight, and its pilot cockpit will be strengthened and equipped with new equipment to resist missile attacks, thus increasing the probability of battlefield survival; it will be equipped with more powerful generators to power more complex airborne electronic equipment; its photoelectric system will be upgraded to be able to detect and identify more distant battlefield targets; the new light multi-purpose missile equipped with mainly attacking armoured combat vehicles and reinforced concrete fortifications will have a range of up to 20 kilometers, about twice the range of similar missiles used in active service in Russia; and its defense weapons and communication equipment will be used to the maximum extent with the Mi-28NM helicopter gunship that can attack air targets, thus making related maintenance simple and economical.
In addition, Ka-52M will have more advanced electronic guidance system, weapon aiming system and navigation equipment.
Russian experts also said that it is worth noting that the Ka-52M will be equipped with communication equipment to communicate with UAVs, so as to obtain information transmitted by nearby UAVs in the air in real time, such as displaying images taken by UAVs on the cockpit screen of the helicopter.
According to the plan, the pilot of Ka-52M can directly control the drone with which he works, thus improving the pilot's mastery of the battlefield situation and guidance of long-range missiles.
According to Russian media reports, Russian Deputy Defense Minister Krivoruchko said in December last year that the Russian Defense Ministry planned to purchase more than 110 Wushu-52Ms by 2027.
