Hebei has replenished 1.75 billion cubic meters of river and lake ecological water since this year.
Xinhua News Agency Shijiazhuang, July 26 (Reporter Wang Kun) The reporter learned from the Hebei Water Conservancy Department that since this year, Hebei Province has implemented ecological water recharge to 28 rivers, including Hutuo River, Tanghe River, Xiangma River and Baiyangdian, making overall use of the water from the diversion river and local reservoirs, with a total of 1.75 billion cubic meters of ecological water recharge completed.
Hebei Province has grasped the favorable opportunity of the South-to-North Water Diversion Project to increase the flow of water and carried out ecological water recharge to rivers such as Tanghe, Shahe and Xuelong River.
At the same time, nine large and medium-sized reservoirs such as the Western Ocean, Dongwu Shi and Baiyangdian have been used to carry out ecological water recharge to rivers such as Liuyang River and Qinglong River, with a cumulative surface area of more than 90 square kilometers.
In order to do a good job in ecological water recharge, the Hebei Water Conservancy Department actively organizes and carries out the investigation of hidden dangers of recharge rivers, remediation and strengthening, and river cleaning, refines practical measures, and strengthens inspection and pipe protection.
Through supervision and inspection and centralized unannounced visits, various problems were solved in time to ensure the safety and order of river recharge.
According to the relevant person in charge of the Hebei Water Conservancy Department, the orderly implementation of river and lake ecological water recharge has effectively restored the river and lake ecological environment in Hebei Province, promoted the recharge and conservation of coastal groundwater, greatly improved the human settlements and economic development environment along the route, and is of great significance to the realization of the river and lake management and protection goal of "clear water, green shore, smooth river and beautiful scenery."
