"Scrambling to the South of the River" Seeking Poetic "Yellow River Dream" - China New Zealand
(The Story of Poverty Reduction in China) Seeking the Poetic "Yellow River Dream" by "Scrambling Jiangnan"
Yinchuan, China News Service, July 26 (Yang Di): "The Jiuqu Yellow River is thousands of miles of sand, and the waves come from the horizon."
The Yellow River, which has aroused the pride of countless literati, Chizi, has given birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain. Now, Ningxia, which has the reputation of "plugging into the south of the Yangtze River", is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority and green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River Dream".
The "Bibo Dream" of River Clear Water Show
"The Yellow River in the world enriches Ningxia," and the Yellow River flows 397 kilometers through Ningxia, which is the "mother river" that nurtures one side.
However, with the rapid progress of industrialization and urbanization, there is an imbalance between the development, utilization, management and protection of rivers and lakes, and chaos such as exceeding the standard of sewage discharge, surrounding lakes for farmland and encroaching on water areas has emerged, resulting in black odor of water bodies, exceeding the standard of water quality, dirty environment and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the diverse restoration of water ecology and making efforts to return the Yellow River to Xiuhe Qing.
Water treatment should start at the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local government has adopted the method of "bid raising + pollution control + strict control." All sewage from industrial parks has been centrally treated, all urban sewage treatment plants have achieved Class I A standard discharge, and black odour water bodies in urban built-up areas have been basically eliminated. The third batch of China's black odour water demonstration cities has been successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake long-term system in 2017. Now, the five-level river and lake long-term responsibility system in districts, counties and villages has been fully covered, and river and lake governors have become the norm.
Gu Jincheng, 64, who lives in a village on the edge of the Yellow River, witnessed the changes of the Yellow River: "The water used to have a stink, but after treatment, the stink is gone."
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is better and his life is more comfortable. Now he often goes for a walk by the Yellow River with his family to feel the blue sky and blue water.
The "Wetland Dream" of Sardines
Flying birds, green trees, trestle roads, clear water... Fan Zhongyun's beautiful scenery of "gathering sand" has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia. A variety of wetlands, such as river wetlands, lake wetlands and swamp wetlands, have been formed along the way, which play an important role in promoting the rational utilization of water resources and water ecological balance, and have also become an important international migration route for birds.
Since 2009, the relevant departments in Ningxia have invested a total of about 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects. At present, the area of Yinchuan wetland is 19,200 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%. There are nearly 200 natural lakes and swamp wetlands, and there are five national wetland parks, one national urban wetland park, six regional wetland parks and eight municipal parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, especially in birds. "The remaining gulls are an endangered bird. There are only more than 20,000 in the world, of which more than 2,000 live in Yinchuan Wetland."
At the same time, Ningxia has designated a 500-meter red line for the wetland protection area on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River according to law, stipulating that no unit or individual may carry out development, construction or business activities within the protection scope except for public welfare projects.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, said that through the management of pollution sources, the comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology and the construction of terminal wetlands, the water quality of the nine main Yellow Drains in Ningxia has reached 100% of the Class IV standard. "Now the water is clear, the fish are swimming and the flowers are blooming."
Pu Huiminsheng's "Drinking Water Dream"
Yinchuan City in Ningxia once had an "awkward" title: the only city along the Yellow River that "watches the Yellow River for water shortage."
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been facing the persistent problem of water shortage during the summer peak. The "pain of water shortage" in the past decade has become a painful summer experience for many residents on high floors. However, under the current situation that major water sources are at the limit of overmining and a large area of groundwater overmining funnel area has been formed underground in the urban area, water scarcity has become a difficult problem perplexing Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking the purified Yellow River has become a good solution to the drinking water problem of local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of Yinchuan Municipal Water Bureau, said that in order to improve the living and production water demand of Yinchuan urban and rural residents, Ningxia launched the Yinchuan Urban Area West Line Water Supply Project in time to replace the original underground water source with the high-quality Yellow River.
"On December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially provided water to the three districts of Yinchuan City. In 2020, the residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank the Yellow River."
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan water conservancy department will give overall consideration to the integrated transformation of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply. "In the next step, we will integrate all the decentralized rural water supply points into the western line water supply project, and we expect to basically realize the integrated urban and rural water supply in Yinchuan region by the end of this year."
