Shenzhen Public Consultation on the Introduction of Health Regulations - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (reporters Mao Siqian and Bai Yu) encourages residents to do medical check-ups frequently to find out problems as soon as possible; prohibits the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors; establishes an online game health review system; and employers should have part-time health managers... Recently, the Health Regulations of the Shenzhen Special Economic Zone (Consultation Draft) were officially released, and Shenzhen residents will have their own "health law."
In order to encourage residents to do medical examination frequently and find out problems at an early date, the above-mentioned consultation draft proposes that the health department should draw up a basic catalogue of health medical examination items according to different age, occupation and other factors.
The health examination expenses falling within the scope of the basic catalogue of health examination items shall be paid by the Social Medical Insurance Co-ordinating Fund according to the standard of one person per year.
The consultation draft makes it clear that the employing unit should rationally allocate human resources, arrange the working hours of employees, implement a rotation system for employees with heavy mental and physical labor load, avoid excessive loss of human function or injury to their physical and mental health, and strictly implement the system of paid leave for employees.
In addition, employers should have full-time and part-time health management personnel and organize and carry out employee health check-ups on a regular basis.
With regard to the physical and mental health of minors, the consultation draft proposes that the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors is prohibited, and the sales location of alcoholic beverages is restricted. Those who violate the regulations will be ordered by the market supervision and administration department to make corrections and fined 30,000 yuan.
Besides "temperance," minors should also "exercise more."
According to the requirements of the consultation draft, the school should arrange students' sports activities for more than one hour every day.
With regard to online games, the departments of public security, culture, radio, tourism, sports, network supervision, health and other departments should improve the health supervision system of Internet service business places, establish the health examination system of online games, and create a good communication space and culture for the healthy growth of young people.
In addition, the consultation draft also proposed that influenza patients must wear masks when entering and leaving public places, and that medical and health institutions should be fined 20,000 yuan for disclosing patients' privacy without consent.
It is worth noting that, in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the consultation draft also requires all departments in Shenzhen to evaluate the impact of the implementation of public policies on the health of the population before formulating plans and normative documents related to urban spatial planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource development and utilization, ecological and environmental protection, and biomedical industry development, as well as approving major construction projects and implementing major public service projects.
If it has not been evaluated or will have a serious adverse impact on urban public health or residents' health, it shall not be enacted or approved for implementation.
