"The so-called molten salt tower photothermal power generation is the concentrated reflection of sunlight through the mirror to the heat absorption tower to form thermal energy, which is then converted into electrical energy through traditional power generation technology."
Zhang Yong, deputy general manager of CLP Hami Solar Thermal Power Generation Co., Ltd, introduced that its design principle is similar to that of solar stoves used in rural areas of northwest China, which gather sunlight.
