Is it "retaliatory" to save money after "90 years" of declining income?
With the income of balance treasure falling, "after 90" not only did not escape balance treasure, but began to "retaliate" to save money?
According to the Report on Saving Money after 90 Years of Balance Treasure (2020 edition) released by the China Institute of New Economics and Alipay, in the first half of the year, "after 90 years" people prefer to save money: the amount of money saved per capita increased by nearly 40% compared with 2019.
Interestingly, "after 90 years," people tend to start with a small amount of money, with 60% saving less than 20 yuan on average...
Saving money with balance treasure has also become the saving habit of "after 90 years."
According to the data, 134 million of the 700 million balance treasure users are "after 90 years."
There are 174 million "post-90" in China, that is, about three out of every four "post-90" in the country are saving money with the balance.
At present, the seven-day annualized yield of money funds such as Balance Bank has fallen to about 1.5% from above 2% at the beginning of the year.
Even so, it did not affect the pace of saving money after "90."
Under the background of improving the "saving effect" of balance treasure, many young people who are used to using balance treasure are also directly transformed into "basic people."
Alipay data shows that as of July 13, the number of new "basic people" on Alipay has more than doubled year-on-year, and more and more young people have achieved "advanced" financial management on Alipay.
Some analysts believe that the flow of funds from the balance to the stock market is also an important reason for the clear decline in the share of the IMF in June.
The report also shows that after the "90s," girls tend to save more money, with an average of 20% higher than the amount of money saved by boys. Of the users who hold funds on Alipay platform, 60% are men, and women tend to choose a more prudent way of managing money than men.
After saving money, what is the plan after 90?
Alipay data shows that "after 90 years," users have the habit of saving money for the goal, with the most users taking travel as the goal.
