The report said that the shared accommodation market has been warming since March.
According to the "China Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020" (hereinafter referred to as the "Report") released by the Sharing Economic Research Center of the National Information Center, the transaction volume of China's shared accommodation market declined by 72.1% year on year in the first five months of 2020 due to the impact of the epidemic.
However, the shared accommodation market began to pick up since March, and the market turnover, order volume and reception number gradually recovered.
According to the Report, the sharp decline in the transaction volume of the shared accommodation market is due, on the one hand, to the sharp decline in the demand for travel and accommodation under the prevention and control of the epidemic, the sharp decrease in the number of orders, the total number of orders in the first five months decreased by 65% year-on-year and the number of receptions decreased by 63% year-on-year. On the other hand, the weak demand also led to a relatively obvious decline in overnight prices, with the average overnight price in the previous five months falling by 16% year-on-year.
However, in March, April and May, the volume of market transactions increased by 78%, 199% and 35% respectively; the number of orders increased by 141%, 152% and 50% respectively; and the number of receptions increased by 81%, 112% and 28% respectively.
The Report points out that the development of shared accommodation industry has been promising for a long time, but there are still many uncertainties in the near future.
