The reporter learned at the meeting that vascular disease is the leading cause of death in China and that the aorta, as the main artery of all human organs, flows from the heart to the whole body and plays an important role.
The occurrence of aortic diseases is often accompanied by high risk, high mortality rate and high difficulty of treatment. The diameter of the thickest section of the aorta is up to 4 cm. Once a hemangioma is formed, rupture occurs, or the rupture of the endometrium produces dissection, it will cause heavy bleeding, which is very dangerous.
In recent years, with the change of people's lifestyle and the acceleration of the pace of life, China has become the world's largest country of hypertension, and the number of aortic diseases has increased. Nowadays, with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
Doctors can "reroute" the blood flow properly by puncture from the thigh and placement of a stent in the aorta, so as to avoid the impact on aneurysms or ruptured dissections and achieve good treatment results. Some operations even require only local anesthesia.
The symposium invited more than ten domestic experts to discuss the new progress in the treatment of aortic diseases, and conducted cutting-edge technical training and difficult case discussion in the form of conference salon.
The reporter learned at the meeting that with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
