The longest high-speed rail tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area
2020-07-26 17: 34: 48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Responsibility Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the XiaoThree Gorges Tunnel construction site.
China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Company
China News Service Chongqing July 26 (reporter Han Lu) The reporter learned from China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Co., Ltd. on July 26 that the 18.9-kilometer-long Zhengwang High-speed Railway XiaoThree Gorges Tunnel was fully connected that day.
It is understood that the Little Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed rail tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area, but also the longest single-hole double-track high-speed rail tunnel designed to reach an speed of 350 km / h in the project under construction in China.
The Zhengwang high-speed railway is located in the three provinces and cities of Henan, Hubei and Chongqing. It connects the Beijing-Canton and Xulan high-speed railway in Zhengzhou to the north, and the Yuwang high-speed railway in Wanzhou to Chongqing in the south. It is an important part of the "eight vertical and eight horizontal" high-speed railway network along the river and the Hainan Tong Road.
The XiaoThree Gorges Tunnel of Zhengwan High-speed Railway was fully opened on the 26th.
The picture shows the scene.
The Zhengwang high-speed railway starts in Zhengzhou, Henan Province, and runs southwest via Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, Xiangyang City, Hubei Province, to Wanzhou District, Chongqing. The new line is about 818 kilometers long, with a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, and about 184 kilometers in Chongqing.
Among them, the Zhengzhou to Xiangyang section has been opened for operation on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up construction.
The XiaoThree Gorges Tunnel, which runs through the entire line on the 26th, is a control project for the entire line of Zhengwang high-speed railway. The project is located at the junction of Fengjie and Wushan counties in Chongqing, with a total length of 18.9 kilometers and a maximum buried depth of 890 meters.
The tunnel started construction in February 2017 and was fully connected on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Jun, head of Zhengwang High-speed Railway Tunnel Design, China Railway Second Academy Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the survey and design party, the topography and geological conditions of the location of the Little Three Gorges Tunnel are very complex, facing risks such as karst, mud inrush and large deformation of soft rock. It is a Grade I high-risk tunnel, which is very difficult to design and construct.
"During the construction of the project, we used geological survey, geophysical exploration and advanced drilling to advance geological prediction, and adopted special design schemes for more than 30 caves of various types. For example, we designed and built a 24-meter-long bridge to cross a large cave with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel to avoid tunnel settlement," said the Royal Army.
According to the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, the construction party, the tunnel is constructed by combining diversion and blocking, ensuring the orderly progress of the project and avoiding the damage of construction drainage to the water body of the Little Three Gorges Scenic Area through the construction of horizontal tunnel guidance, grouting to block water, strengthening the structural support of the tunnel and building a sewage treatment station. At the same time, it has successfully overcome the construction difficulties such as the large deformation of soft rock up to 7 kilometers long and the multi-mud inrush with a maximum daily inrush of 157,000 cubic meters.
When the full line of Zhengwang high-speed railway is completed and opened to traffic, it will become a new convenient and fast main passenger transport route from the southwest to the Central Plains, North China and Northeast China. It is of great significance to improve the capacity and quality of the northeast-bound railway passage in the southwest, improve the layout of the regional road network, accelerate the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the route, promote the coordinated development of the region, and promote the implementation of the western development strategy.
