The overall stability of employment and prices highlights the "temperature" of the economy
Economic Daily China Economic Network reporter Lin Fengcang
In the first half of this year, in the face of the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic, China coordinated efforts to promote the prevention and control of the epidemic and economic and social development. The situation of epidemic prevention and control continued to improve, the steady economic recovery trend was obvious, the employment and price performance closely related to people's livelihood were generally stable, and the Chinese economy handed over a warm economic performance report card.
The survey unemployment rate rose in the first two months of this year.
Especially in February, the production and operation activities of many enterprises were basically shut down, the demand for employment of enterprises decreased, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the surveyed unemployment rate in cities and towns rose.
As the situation of epidemic prevention and control gradually improved, the order of production and life of the whole society was constantly restored.
The CPC Central Committee adheres to the general tone of stability and progress, further strengthens macro-policy hedging, comprehensively strengthens employment priority policies, and actively promotes the work of helping enterprises stabilize and expand employment.
China has increased its policy of hedging stable jobs, played a combination of policies of "relief and deferred compensation," phased reduction and reduction of the contribution portion of three social insurance units, allowed deferred payment of social insurance premiums, expanded the benefits of stable return of unemployment insurance for small and medium-sized and micro-sized enterprises, and provided employment absorption subsidies and trainee subsidies to enterprises to absorb key groups.
With the implementation of various stable employment policies, the employment demand of enterprises has steadily recovered, the employment situation has gradually improved, and the surveyed unemployment rate in cities and towns has gradually decreased. In June, the surveyed unemployment rate was 5.7%.
Zhang Yi, director of the Population and Employment Statistics Department of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to bear fruit, and the labor force who had withdrawn from the previous period due to the impact of the epidemic returned successively. The urban labor force participation rate in June increased by about 10 percentage points compared with February, which was close to the same period last year.
According to the data, the total number of urban employment in June increased by more than 19% compared with February, and most industries reached the pre-epidemic level; the average working week of employees in enterprises reached 46.8 hours, 6.6 hours higher than in February and 0.1 hours higher than in January.
Prices also affect families.
In January this year, the year-on-year increase in CPI was 5.4%, a new high in many years.
In February, although the year-on-year increase in CPI fell slightly, it was still in the "5 range."
The year-on-year increase in CPI was at a high level, driven by consumer demand before the Spring Festival, the wrong month of the Spring Festival and the low year-on-year base.
However, the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic on prices is particularly obvious.
Influenced by the epidemic prevention and control, in January and February, all parts of the country experienced delays in logistics, untimely supply of goods and materials, and increased transportation costs of materials. In addition, some citizens hoarded and rushed to buy, resulting in a marked increase in the prices of some necessities of life.
In order to cope with the disturbance caused by epidemic prevention and control to the price situation, the relevant departments have included important living materials in the scope of emergency transportation guarantee to ensure the smooth transportation of materials.
Under the influence of a series of policy measures, the market supply of vegetables, melons and fruits has been effectively guaranteed.
In order to cope with the rapid rise in pork prices at the beginning of this year, after the Central Government introduced the policy of ensuring supply and stabilizing prices, all regions and departments quickly implemented it, significantly improved the supply of pork reserves, orderly recovery of pig production capacity, and gradually normal production and marketing order.
Since March, pork prices have declined continuously, and the year-on-year increase in food prices fell to 10.6% in May. In June, pork prices rose slightly in the ring ratio due to factors such as the slowdown in the exit of pigs, the reduction of imports and the recovery of group consumption demand.
The seasonal variation of fresh vegetable prices is obvious, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Influenced by the high comparison base in the same period last year, fresh fruit prices continued to decline year-on-year, with an average decline of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic livelihood of the masses is effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation remains stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation and logistics, all regions have increased their guarantee, and the market supply and demand situation has improved.
Since March, the CPI has declined for four consecutive months, and the year-on-year increase has also fallen from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June, and the overall price level has returned to stability.
In the second half of the year, China's prices will continue to maintain a moderate level, with little overall inflationary pressure, but we should still promote the restoration of the order of production and life on the premise of normalizing epidemic prevention and control.
We should effectively deal with natural disasters such as floods and droughts in the main producing areas of grain, fruits and vegetables and other agricultural products, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on acts that disrupt market order such as hoarding and inflating prices.
