"Doctor of China" to pay tribute to anti-epidemic heroes - Xinhua News
Recently, with the respect of the heroes of Chinese filmmakers fighting the epidemic, the chairman of Bona Pictures Group and director Liu Weiqiang (left) held a discussion and exchange with Academician Zhong Nanshan in Guangzhou on the filming and production of the anti-epidemic film Doctor of China.
Bona Films hopes to use Doctor of China to pay tribute to all the medical and epidemic prevention workers fighting on the front line of epidemic prevention and control!
In 2021, the film will be released nationwide as a gift film to celebrate the 100th anniversary of the founding of the Communist Party of China.
At present, under the arrangement and deployment of the Ministry of Propaganda of China and the National Film Bureau, and with the support of the Guangdong Film Bureau and the Hubei Film Bureau, Bona Films is organizing the original team of the film Captain of China to prepare the film Doctor of China, which is a film that reflects the unity of the people of the whole country in fighting the new crown pneumonia epidemic under the strong leadership of the Party Central Committee.
Focusing on the anti-epidemic front line in Wuhan, the film will show the moving stories of Chinese medical personnel full of dedication and sacrifice on the anti-epidemic front line from the perspective of human nature, using unique narrative and powerful lens language.
It is understood that on the first day of the unsealed Wuhan, Boehner Company overcame many difficulties and sent a photography team to go deep into the front line of the epidemic, exchange face-to-face understanding with hundreds of medical workers and collect information. At present, it has interviewed the white angels at the forefront of the anti-epidemic front, including Academician Zhong Nanshan himself, the first person in Guangzhou to help Wuhan, the Guangdong medical team to help Austria, as well as Wuhan Yintan Hospital, Wuhan Association Hospital, Wuhan University Central Hospital and Wuhan Central Hospital, and taken a large number of valuable first-hand video materials.
Academician Zhong Nanshan also raised expectations and hopes for the filming of the film at the symposium: "I am looking forward to it. I hope you will not only visit some experts who have made more appearances, but also interview more medical personnel working hard on the front line, who are the majority."
He said that he had seen "Me and My Motherland" and "Chinese Captain" before, and thought it was a good way to tell large-scale stories from the perspective of ordinary people.
"Now some foreign friends still have some misunderstandings about China."
When talking about the spread of the film, Academician Zhong Nanshan said that at present, some people in foreign countries like to label the virus as politicized. He hoped that the film would impress the audience from the perspective of human nature: "In addition to being shown in China, it is best to show the film abroad. We should impress the audience with the true humanistic spirit in a way that the audience at home and abroad can understand."
Academician Zhong Nanshan also affectionately recalled the film "Middle-aged People" in the 1980s. "After so many years, what impressed me most about the film after the reform and opening up was" Middle-aged People. "At that time, my friends of doctors abroad cried. If" Chinese Doctors "could play such a role, it would be great."
Academician Zhong Nanshan said that if Doctor of China can resonate with foreign audiences, it will be very successful.
During the discussion and exchange, Academician Zhong Nanshan also shared his opinions and suggestions on the current international epidemic prevention and control. "I believe people will always be smarter than viruses."
Academician Zhong Nanshan said that although the virus is difficult to predict, since the primitive society, human beings have passed through many difficulties and risks. Now that modern society has developed medical science and technology and social management measures, and medical personnel and even the common people all over the world have a basic understanding of the scientific response to the new crown pneumonia epidemic, people will no longer be as passive as before. "Next, we should pay attention to two aspects of work, one is to study how the world can strengthen cooperation, the other is to pay attention to soothe people's hearts."
