Telecom network fraud crime rose by 70% in the first half of the year.
According to the Supreme Inspection website, in the first half of this year, procuratorial organs across the country prosecuted a total of 5,8101 people for fraud crimes, up 35% year on year.
In particular, the number of fraud crimes prosecuted by procuratorial organs accounted for 43.4% of the total number of crimes against epidemic prevention and control.
The Supreme People's Procuratorate has carried out targeted guidance. Of the 10 typical cases related to epidemic prevention and control that have been issued, a total of 9 involve the crime of fraud.
Judging from the cases handled by the procuratorial organs in the first half of the year, there are a wide range of fraud-related crimes, ranging from the national macro-policy to the people's food, clothing and housing, including epidemic-related fraud, "medical care" fraud, "health products" fraud, "enrollment agency" fraud, "arbitrage loan" fraud, "state subsidy fraud, national assets unfreezing fraud, etc., which are constantly" new "and cover many fields, including education, medical care, employment, old age, social security, land requisition and demolition, accurate poverty alleviation, and financial credit, which not only cause economic losses to the victims, but also seriously affect economic and social development.
In particular, some telecommunications network frauds break through the restrictions of national boundaries, regions and personnel, and have the characteristics of stakeholders, cross-border, remote and electronic payment. There are many victims and great harm.
For example, some have set up special companies, rented high-grade office buildings, set up multiple departments or posts, used legal network platforms to publicize and recruit, trained and evaluated recruiters, and adopted enterprise operation mode management, wearing the cloak of "legality" and becoming more attractive.
It is incumbent upon the procuratorial organs to punish and prevent crimes according to law and issue timely early warning to the public and relevant departments.
In judicial cases, the procuratorial organs conscientiously perform their duties, not only maintaining a high-pressure posture against fraud crimes, but also refining various law enforcement measures in a targeted manner, and promoting social governance through the production and issuance of procuratorial suggestions.
The procuratorial organs strictly regard the facts, evidence, procedure and application of the law in mass arrest and prosecution of fraud cases, take the facts as the basis and the law as the criterion, and do their utmost.
Especially for the crime of telecom network fraud, we pay attention to the central role of electronic data in fact determination, and strive to build a chain of evidence between electronic data, verbal evidence and documentary evidence.
For example, in response to an epidemic-related fraud case handled by the Yinzhou District Public Prosecutor's Office of Ningbo City, Zhejiang Province, the procuratorial organ intervened in advance at the first time. It took only five days from the occurrence of the case to its conclusion, reflecting the attitude and determination to handle the case quickly and strictly and maintain the overall social stability.
In the examination of arrest and prosecution, attention should be paid to the prosecution of missing offenders, the omission of 733 persons by the public security organs and the omission of 1,113 co-offenders by the public security organs.
In the first half of the year, procuratorial organs across the country issued 298 procuratorial proposals for fraud crimes, promoting joint efforts to prevent fraud crimes and promote in-depth governance.
For example, in view of the loopholes found in the supervision of telecommunications networks by communications enterprises, banks and intermediary organizations in the handling of cases, the Guangzhou Public Prosecutor's Office and the Dongguan Public Prosecutor's Office of Guangdong Province put forward timely procuratorial suggestions, urging the relevant units to strengthen supervision and improve the mechanism to help promote the construction of a long-term system.
Fourth, make every effort to do a good job in the recovery of spoils and losses.
Procuratorial organs all over the country seize the important links such as intervening in the investigation, guiding the taking of evidence, examining and prosecuting, urge the investigation organs to actively recover the stolen funds, cooperate with the relevant departments to do a good job in the recovery of spoils and damages, and strive to minimize the economic losses caused to the people by the crime of fraud.
For example, the Lin-certain arbitrage loan case handled by the Beijing Public Prosecutor's Office involved 22 properties waiting to be sealed up. In the case that the property may be disposed of first by other cases, the first company issued a "Letter of Suspension of Execution" and served it to the relevant court in time. It suggested that the previously sealed-up court suspend the execution of the property involved and deal with it uniformly until the facts of the crime are found out, so as to make its best efforts to recover the property involved and recover the losses of the victims.
The procurator reminded everyone to be very alert to the crime of fraud. Don't expect "pie in the sky," and don't believe it cheaply and keep your "money bag."
Yuna Town, Weining County, Guizhou Province: Shorter apple trees widen the way out of poverty
2020-07-26 11: 42: 58 Source: China Economic Network Author: Zhu Yanjing Responsibility Editor: Zhu Yanjing
In the heat, the reporter of Economic Daily-China Economic Network walked into Zhonghai Village, Jina Town, Weining County, Guizhou Province.
In the hot sun, Li Yuanzhong, a villager, was weeding grass in the base. Although his face was red, his mouth hummed a few songs from time to time.
Weining County, where Yuna Town is located, is well known in the surrounding areas because of its low latitude, high altitude, abundant light, large temperature difference between day and night, high sugar content and good taste of apples, but also because of its small size and many spots, it has not been able to sell at a good price and has not formed an industrial scale.
Yuna Town was once a poor town with "Baogu potato for spring and autumn." Ten years ago, the local poverty incidence rate was as high as 25.8%.
It is urgent to change the traditional planting habits, adjust the industrial structure and increase farmers' income during the critical period when the fight against poverty eradication enters a decisive battle.
After many visits, Chen Chao, secretary of the Party Committee of Yuna Town, and a team of people in the town believed that the industrial development could no longer follow the old path.
To this end, Yuna Town introduced leading enterprises to grow apples in a modern way.
Hou Jianwen, deputy general manager of Weining Beyond Agriculture Co., Ltd. came to Jina Town from Shaanxi Province in 2015 to investigate. He saw the local planting conditions at a glance and began to plant apple trees there in 2016.
At first, the village mobilized Li Yuanzhong to transfer the land to plant apple trees. Li Yuanzhong and his wife murmured in their hearts, "After planting apples for so many years, they didn't see who in the village made a fortune by planting apples."
"All the apples grown are dwarf apples and will not make the tree grow too tall."
What Li Yuanzhong did not expect was that a new method was used for apple planting. Irrigation pipes were spread under each apple tree, and water and fertilizer were poured to the roots. When the fruit was harvested in autumn, the tractor drove directly into the orchard and the fruit could be picked standing.
At present, Apple base has gradually entered a period of high production, and the market is as expected by Hou Jianwen. Apple does not worry about selling and is loved by consumers in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and other cities.
The growing apple industry has brought new changes to Li Yuanzhong's life. Although he is still planting land, he has a new source of income.
Li Yuanzhong's family transferred more than 9 acres of land to the Apple base. In addition to the guaranteed land transfer fee, there are profit dividends after hanging fruit every year. The couple usually work in the base. "One person gets 80 yuan a day and has work all year round."
Li Yuanzhong told the reporter that the profit dividend earned more than 2,800 yuan last year. Combined with the land transfer fee and the husband and wife's work income, the family earned more than 80,000 yuan. "We can't worry about food and clothing, and we have a well-off life."
"At present, it has begun to show results. The annual output value of an acre of apples exceeds 15,000 yuan, about 10 times that of corn."
Chen Chao told the reporter that at present, 20,000 mu of apples have been planted in the whole town of Qena, and there are 6,000 mu in Zhonghai Village alone, covering 4,056 rural households and 17,200 people, including 656 poor households and 2,952 people with built-up cards, with a salary of more than 6 million yuan a year.
With increasingly bulging pockets, Li Yuanzhong also began to realize his "wish."
This Lunar New Year, Li Yuanzhong bought a Land Cruiser and now drives his car to and from work every day. "There are still more than ten acres of land in his home. When the next step is to expand the scale of the Apple base and transfer it all to them, the income will be more."
