Membrane separation technology helps crack the "greenhouse effect" -CNS
Membrane separation technology helps crack the "greenhouse effect"
Diagram of new hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology
Our reporter Shang Rui reported: Recently, the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team of Tianjin University made significant progress in "capturing carbon dioxide by membrane separation," and successfully developed a new hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology to greatly improve the carbon dioxide capture performance of membrane materials.
The relevant results have been published as the cover article of the international journal Greenhouse Gases: Science and Technology.
The "greenhouse effect" is a major environmental problem perplexing human development, and carbon dioxide emissions are the culprit of the "greenhouse effect."
How to efficiently capture and utilize the carbon dioxide emitted by human beings is the focus of scientists.
"Membrane separation method" is a new carbon dioxide capture technology. It separates carbon dioxide gas with the help of membrane material, which has the characteristics of high efficiency, energy saving and simple operation.
How to make membrane materials "breathe deeply" and improve the efficiency of gas separation is the bottleneck and difficulty of capturing carbon dioxide by membrane separation method.
The research team of Tianjin University has innovative ideas to explore the influence of different solvents on the separation performance of membrane gas through repeated experiments.
The experimental results show that using N-methylpyrrolidone as the preparation solvent, the carbon nanotubes in the film material are more evenly distributed and "more breathable," effectively improving the gas separation efficiency and rate of the film material.
The carbon dioxide separation performance of hybrid matrix films prepared by this new technology is close to the upper limit of theoretical separation of such membrane materials.
"The new technology provides a new idea for capturing carbon dioxide by membrane separation."
Li Run, a member of the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team of Tianjin University, said, "We hope this technology can provide strong support for the treatment of flue gas by coal-fired power plants and chemical enterprises in the future and play an important role in controlling greenhouse gas emissions."
Understand what professional grade difference is before filing a voluntary report.
2020-07-27 02: 22: 36 Source: Chongqing Morning Post Author: Yu xiao Responsibility Editor: Yu xiao
Understand what professional grade difference is before filing
Every year, some students or parents do not understand the nouns involved in the voluntary filing, which affects the voluntary filing.
This year, five colleges and universities of Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University and Beijing Chemical University jointly issued the admission policy for 2020, eliminating professional grade difference.
What is the meaning of professional grade difference and what is the significance in the voluntary filing?
There are three ways of professional assignment rules
Experts reminded that before volunteering, one must read the Admission Charter of the desired school in detail and understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the transfer ratio and the rules of professional allocation.
The rules of professional assignment mean that after the transfer of colleges and universities, there are three main ways for professional admission: professional priority, score priority and professional grade difference.
The specific method used by colleges and universities will be specified in the Admission Charter.
However, the admission principle of some colleges and universities is that the total score is preferred, and there is no grade difference between majors.
That is, the candidates in the admission range will be queued according to the total score. When the score does not reach the voluntary admission score of the first major, it will depend on whether the voluntary admission score of the second major has been reached, and so on until the admission to the last professional volunteer, there is no grade difference between the professional volunteers.
The so-called "professional grade difference" means that when institutions arrange candidates for majors, they determine the admission majors of volunteer candidates for different majors according to one or more scores published in the admission rules. This score value is "professional grade difference."
That is, the difference in the scores between the first professional volunteer and the non-first professional volunteer, and the difference in the scores between the volunteers in each major, such as 3, 2 and 1.
For example.
It is assumed that Xiao Ming, a student, applied for the examination of A University and received 560 points. His professional volunteers are: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering and e-commerce. The method of professional grade difference is implemented for the admission of A University. The grade difference is divided into 2, 1, 1 and 0.
In the professional assignment, if Xiaoming's first major volunteer meets the professional admission requirements and the major has a planned balance, Xiaoming will be admitted to the "Computer" major; if the computer is not admitted, his score will be subtracted by 2 points, and the results of 558 points will be ranked with the candidates who volunteer to apply for the "International Trade" examination of the first major to determine whether they meet the professional admission conditions; if they are still not satisfied, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 557 points) for the voluntary "automated" admission of the third major; if they are still not satisfied, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 556 points) for the admission of the fourth major, and if the follow-up major is still unable to meet its professional volunteers, the score will not be subtracted, and so on.
Different professional grade differences in different universities
With the popularization of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have eliminated professional grade differences, but some colleges and universities have retained this method this year. According to the Admission Charter published by each school, more than 20 universities have set professional grade differences this year.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight Academy, etc.
In these colleges and universities, the professional grade difference set by each university is different.
Some colleges and universities have grade differences in each major, such as Ningxia University. The candidates whose files have been submitted to this university will be admitted according to the order in which the candidates fill in the professional volunteers by decreasing by one point and then by the grade.
Some universities set different professional grade differences between different majors.
For example, in Jimei University, the total score difference between professional volunteers is 4 points, that is, the difference between the first professional volunteers and other professional volunteers is 3 points, there is no difference between other professional volunteers, which is regarded as parallel volunteers, and the difference between other professional volunteers and adjustment professional volunteers is 1 point.
When volunteering, candidates and their parents must carefully read the admission policy of the reported school to see if there is any professional grade difference and what the form of grade difference is. While giving full consideration to the scores, they should also make a reasonable analysis of the schools and majors to be selected. If the institution explicitly adopts the method of grade difference in the admission charter, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between the majors and improve the admission probability.
